ZH: 我们不应该只是抱怨，而是应该采取行动来解决问题。
EN: We should not just complain, but instead take action to solve the problem.

ZH: 她总是向我倾诉她的怨言和烦恼。
EN: She always pours out her complaints and frustrations to me.

ZH: 他对办公室里的怨言充耳不闻，只专注于自己的工作。
EN: He turns a deaf ear to the office grumbling and focuses only on his work.

ZH: 她的怨言让整个氛围变得压抑和消极。
EN: Her complaints create a gloomy and negative atmosphere.

ZH: 我们应该不抱怨，而是要讲求感恩之心。
EN: Instead of complaining, we should practice gratitude.

ZH: 这样的怨言徒增困扰，却无法改变现状。
EN: Such complaints only add to the troubles, without changing the situation.

ZH: 她口无遮拦，经常把自己的怨言公之于众。
EN: She has no filter and often expresses her grievances publicly.

ZH: 消极的怨言只会拖累你前进的步伐。
EN: Negative complaints will only drag down your progress.

ZH: 我想说出我心中的怨言，但我知道这样并不会改善什么。
EN: I want to express the complaints in my heart, but I know it won't improve anything.

ZH: 不要让怨言淹没了你对事情的正面看法。
EN: Don't let complaints drown out your positive perspectives on things.

ZH: 我对这个结果感到不满，但我不会抱怨。
EN: I am dissatisfied with the outcome, but I won't complain.

ZH: 遇到挫折时，抱怨只会使我们更加无助。
EN: Complaining will only make us feel more helpless when facing setbacks.

ZH: 只有通过行动，我们才能改变怨言带来的状况。
EN: Only through action can we change the situation created by complaints.

ZH: 别太在意别人的怨言，只要你能做到最好就行。
EN: Don't pay too much attention to others' grumbling, as long as you do your best.

ZH: 怨言不能解决问题，它只会加重负担。
EN: Complaints cannot solve problems; they only add to the burden.

ZH: 她的怨言让团队的合作气氛变得紧张和紧迫。
EN: Her complaints make the teamwork atmosphere tense and urgent.

ZH: 抱怨并不能改变这个结果，我们应该接受并寻找解决办法。
EN: Complaining won't change the outcome; we should accept it and find solutions.

ZH: 他的怨言越来越多，让大家都感到疲倦和沮丧。
EN: His complaints are increasing, making everyone feel tired and frustrated.

ZH: 怨言只会让我们的心情变得更糟，而无法真正解决问题。
EN: Complaining will only make our mood worse without truly solving the problem.

ZH: 别因为小事而抱怨，学会放大心中的感激之情。
EN: Don't complain about trivial matters; learn to magnify the feeling of gratitude in your heart.
